name: Walla Walla Mobile Units
notes:
This clinic will be held at HAPO Community Credit Union (College Place) in the parking lot. 

The clinic will offer PFIZER COVID-19 VACCINE for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over and JOHNSON & JOHNSON COVID-19 VACCINE for all qualifying individuals aged 18 years & older. 

Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 years old, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. 

We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.
************************************************************
Esta clínica se llevará a cabo en HAPO Community Credit Union (College Place) en el estacionamiento.

La clínica ofrecerá la VACUNA PFIZER COVID-19 para todas las personas que califiquen a partir de los 12 años y la VACUNA JOHNSON & JOHNSON COVID-19 para todas las personas que califiquen a partir de los 18 años.

Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los niños de 12 a 17 años, el consentimiento y la firma de los padres / tutores se pueden completar en el sitio o en la pantalla final del proceso de registro en línea.

Esperamos verte. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT FOR 1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Walk-ins are welcome. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) vaccine is also available for people 18 years and older. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA 1ª y 2ª DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante. Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.  La vacuna Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) también está disponible para personas mayores de 18 años.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
BIENVENIDO A WALK-INS. Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
notes: Movies at the Marina, 1022 Marine Dr NE, Olympia, WA, 98501. We will be located at the Port of Olympia. All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

notes: This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. This is a walk-in clinic at the Hands On Children's Museum located at 414 Jefferson St NE, Olympia, WA 98501, for anyone age 12 and older from 10am-2pm. All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
